<div class="section" id="gs-group-messages-hide">
  <h2>Hide a Post</h2>
  <p>
    You and the administrators of a group can hide the posts you have
    made.
    To hide a post carry out the following steps.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li><a href="/p">Log in,</a> if necessary.</li>
    <li>View
    <a href="#gs-group-messages-post">the post on the web.</a></li>
    <li>Click the <samp class="link">Hide post</samp> link.
    The <cite>Hide</cite> form will be shown.</li>
    <li>Enter the reason for hiding the post in the
    <samp class="entry">Reason</samp> entry.</li>
    <li>Click the <samp class="button">Hide</samp> button.
    The post will be hidden, and you be shown the hidden post in
    the topic.
  </ol>
  <p>
    Some information about the post is still available after it has
    been hidden.
    <a href="#gs-group-messages-hide-visible">The table below</a>
    details what can be seen and what is hidden.
  </p>
  <table id="gs-group-messages-hide-visible">
    <caption>What is visible after a post is hidden</caption>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <th style="width:7.615em">Email Messages</th>
        <td>
          The email messages that were sent out to the group members
          when the post was made are still <strong>visible</strong>
          after the post has been hidden.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <th>Post on the Web</th>
        <td>
          Some of the post on the web is hidden.
          <a href="#gs-group-messages-post-metadata">The information
          about the post</a>
          is <strong>visible.</strong>
          This includes who made the post, and when the post was made.
          However,
          <a href="#gs-group-messages-post-body">the body of the
          post</a>
          is <strong>hidden.</strong>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <th>Files</th>
        <td>
          The files that were added as part of the post are
          <strong>hidden.</strong>
          If someone tries to view the file he or she will see an
          error page.
          The error page will show the reason that the post was hidden.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <th>Images</th>
        <td>
          The images that were added as part of the post are
          <strong>hidden.</strong>
          If someone tries to view the file he or she will see an
          error page.
          The error page will show the reason that the post was hidden.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <th>Reason</th>
        <td>
          The reason the post was hidden is <strong>visible</strong>
          to
          <a href="#gs-group-messages-privacy">those that could see the
          post previously.</a>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table><!--gs-group-messages-hide-visible-->
</div><!--gs-group-messages-hide-->
